12:51.751 --> 12:53.842
(quietly):
"My name shall be cast out..."

12:53.843 --> 12:56.112
(continues indistinctly)

12:56.113 --> 12:57.615
Ingrid. Oh.

12:57.616 --> 12:59.954
(laughs): I'm sorry,
I-I didn't mean to scare you.

12:59.959 --> 13:03.257
No, I-I-I was just...
doing some shelving.

13:03.258 --> 13:05.630
But I can finish later.
What's up?

13:05.648 --> 13:08.133
Well, I wanted to come by
and see if you...

13:08.151 --> 13:09.735
wanted to have
dinner tonight.

13:09.736 --> 13:13.369
Dinner? Like a-a date?
Like a dinner date?

13:13.370 --> 13:16.156
Won't that be weird...
you arrested my mom.

13:16.157 --> 13:17.910
I'm actually
off the case now.

13:17.911 --> 13:20.403
- What? Why?
- Because of our history.

13:20.404 --> 13:22.748
My bosses felt there was
a conflict of interest.

13:22.782 --> 13:25.314
Oh. We have a history?

13:25.329 --> 13:27.986
(laughs): Well, I thought
we were friends. (laughs)

13:28.004 --> 13:30.205
Of course. We are...

13:30.256 --> 13:32.091
- Friends.
- Um...

13:32.125 --> 13:33.675
Ingrid...

13:34.184 --> 13:36.795
- I like you.
- Really?

13:36.829 --> 13:40.432
How many times do I have to tell you that
before you start to believe me?

13:40.467 --> 13:43.001
(laughs): Just one more
would probably do it.

13:43.019 --> 13:45.020
I'm kidding.

13:45.055 --> 13:47.306
Have dinner with me.

13:47.340 --> 13:52.051
Now, I won't mention anything about
the case, so we can just talk about...

13:52.136 --> 13:53.503
Magic...

13:53.504 --> 13:55.447
And voodoo spells.
Yeah, I'm a detective;

13:55.482 --> 13:57.616
I notice things. It's...

13:57.650 --> 14:00.922
It's just an academic study
for my dissertation.

14:00.923 --> 14:03.139
Finally gonna finish. Yay!
(laughs)

14:03.155 --> 14:04.567
Good for you.

14:04.568 --> 14:05.952
So, um...

14:06.270 --> 14:07.823
what do you say?

14:08.338 --> 14:11.997
Look, I know you could use a night out,
and you have to eat, right?

14:12.277 --> 14:14.412
Okay. Yes.

14:14.446 --> 14:15.963
Great.

14:15.998 --> 14:17.445
Um...

14:17.797 --> 14:20.910
- Bye.
- Bye. (laughs)

14:20.911 --> 14:23.329
âª

14:23.555 --> 14:26.329
Enjoy.
Hey, can I get a drink?

14:26.345 --> 14:28.983
Get in line, buddy...
I'm kind of in the weeds here.

14:28.984 --> 14:30.138
Who had a margarita?

14:30.139 --> 14:32.160
I ordered a beer, Freya,
like, ten minutes ago.

14:32.161 --> 14:34.250
- And I ordered a mojito.
- Just give me a minute.

14:34.251 --> 14:35.916
Okay, who had the beer?

14:35.917 --> 14:38.172
What are you doing?
You don't work here.

14:38.173 --> 14:40.519
You obviously need help,
so... I'm helping.

14:40.535 --> 14:42.674
- You really shouldn't be back here.
- Can I get a dirty martini?

14:42.708 --> 14:44.618
- Not a problem.
- He's not a bartender.

14:44.619 --> 14:47.978
Relax, I can handle this.
I'm very experienced.

14:47.996 --> 14:51.315
- WOMAN: I'm still waiting for my mojito.
- Can everyone just relax!

14:56.205 --> 14:57.847
What the hell was that?

14:57.902 --> 15:00.150
Uh, stupid shelves.

15:00.151 --> 15:02.602
They do that sometimes.

15:03.379 --> 15:05.046
(crickets chirping)

15:22.492 --> 15:24.993
âª

15:30.212 --> 15:32.297
WHISPERED VOICE:
Joanna.

15:32.348 --> 15:35.300
(gasps):
Oh! Wendy!

15:35.351 --> 15:39.268
- What are you doing in here?!
- Sorry. I'm sorry.

15:39.269 --> 15:40.861
- I'm sorry. I just...
- What...

15:40.862 --> 15:43.751
I thought if I recreated your dream,
then inspiration would strike.

15:43.777 --> 15:46.980
Well... you scared
the crap out of me.

15:46.981 --> 15:48.844
So, I made a list
of your enemies,

15:48.845 --> 15:52.377
and the list is really, really long, and
I still need your help to finish it.

15:52.403 --> 15:54.903
Do you remember anything
in particular about your dream?

15:54.904 --> 15:57.019
Like, did the shifter
have a weapon, or...?

15:57.020 --> 16:00.158
Yeah, she had this strange
little doll made out of hair.

16:00.209 --> 16:02.276
What? Wait.

16:02.294 --> 16:05.080
I can't believe
you ruined my headboard.

16:05.114 --> 16:06.965
Did it look like this?

16:07.549 --> 16:10.469
- Yeah. What is that?
- It's called an energy talisman.

16:10.495 --> 16:12.971
I knew a guy in New Orleans
who used to make these.

16:13.005 --> 16:17.092
Oh, you mean it's one of those low-rent
voodoo things that's supposed to...

16:17.126 --> 16:20.963
- Suck away your powers?
- No, not <i>supposed</i> to, it does.

16:20.964 --> 16:23.263
It only works on the witch
whose hair it's made of.

16:23.264 --> 16:25.966
Don't underestimate this,
Joanna... I've seen it work.

16:25.967 --> 16:28.181
I put a protection spell
around the house.

16:28.182 --> 16:31.686
You put a protection spell around the
entire town, and somebody broke through.

16:31.687 --> 16:34.845
I think you're into major denial
about how serious this is.

16:34.846 --> 16:37.847
I get it. But you've been gone
a long time, Wendy,

16:37.848 --> 16:40.165
and the girls and I
have been doing just fine.

16:40.199 --> 16:42.897
Really? Just fine?
You're on trial for murder,

16:42.898 --> 16:44.750
the shifter has
already killed me once,

16:44.751 --> 16:47.707
tried to kill Freya... it's time
to go on the offensive.

16:47.708 --> 16:50.493
You're not a parent, Wendy.

16:50.755 --> 16:55.456
You don't understand what it is
to be responsible for another person.

16:56.257 --> 16:59.788
Well, I may not be a parent,
Joanna, but I have a family...

16:59.789 --> 17:03.753
a family that I love and I care about.
I'm trying to protect you,

17:03.754 --> 17:05.761
and you're sitting here
doing laundry!

17:05.779 --> 17:09.898
- <i>Your</i> laundry!
- Oh, I'm sorry, let me help you with that!

17:09.933 --> 17:11.983
Uh, very mature.

17:12.035 --> 17:15.079
You know what, you can't bury
your head in the sand forever, Joanna.

17:15.080 --> 17:17.696
If you don't do something soon,
things are gonna get worse.

17:17.698 --> 17:19.648
A lot worse!

17:19.650 --> 17:21.984
(door slams) (groans)

17:25.965 --> 17:27.916
Okay, concentrate.

17:27.951 --> 17:30.252
Come on, Freya, Ingrid
can empty a freaking lake.

17:30.286 --> 17:31.787
You can do this.

17:35.725 --> 17:37.069
(bottle shatters)

17:37.070 --> 17:39.519
Wow. You really are a klutz.

17:39.520 --> 17:41.625
It's kind of adorable.
(sighs)

17:41.626 --> 17:43.349
What are you doing here?

17:43.400 --> 17:45.841
- I work here.
- No, you don't.

17:45.842 --> 17:47.870
Roger was very impressed with
my skills behind the bar.

17:47.904 --> 17:49.989
He offered me a job,
and I took it.

17:50.023 --> 17:52.358
You took it?

17:52.409 --> 17:55.210
- Why would you do that?
- I need the money.

17:55.211 --> 17:58.759
<i>- You</i> need money? Please.
- My family's rich, I'm not.

17:58.760 --> 18:00.320
I don't believe
that for a second.

18:00.321 --> 18:02.962
Well, it's the truth... I haven't
taken a penny off them.

18:03.689 --> 18:07.296
I've spent the last five years teaching
English in Thailand, surfed in Australia,

18:07.297 --> 18:09.058
tended bar
on three continents.

18:09.092 --> 18:12.094
(sighs) I'm just scraping by now
to get to the next destination.

18:12.128 --> 18:13.710
Well, it sounds incredible.

18:13.711 --> 18:15.347
I've always wanted
to do something like that.

18:15.382 --> 18:17.753
Never been out of East End.

18:18.035 --> 18:19.681
Not even once?

18:19.682 --> 18:22.524
Well, when I was a teenager,
I used to sneak out

18:22.525 --> 18:24.919
and go to New York
with my fake I.D.

18:24.937 --> 18:28.356
And I think I went
on a field trip to DC once.

18:28.390 --> 18:30.525
But basically, no.

18:30.559 --> 18:33.261
I was raised by a single mother.
Schoolteacher.

18:33.279 --> 18:35.972
We weren't exactly jetting off
to Paris every week.

18:35.973 --> 18:38.351
Oh, jetting off to Paris
is overrated anyway.

18:38.359 --> 18:40.401
The one thing I learned
in my travels

18:40.435 --> 18:43.071
is you can be miserable
pretty much anywhere.

18:43.105 --> 18:44.539
And happy anywhere, too.

18:44.840 --> 18:47.492
It's about where
you are inside.

18:47.543 --> 18:50.611
Did a monk teach you that
in Nepal or something?

18:50.629 --> 18:53.266
- I think I read it in a fortune cookie.
- (laughs): Right.

18:53.282 --> 18:55.946
But you got to
admit it's true.

18:55.947 --> 18:57.171
If you're not
being honest

18:57.172 --> 18:59.511
about who you are and what you
really want, you could be living

18:59.512 --> 19:01.563
in a mansion
and it wouldn't really matter.

19:02.631 --> 19:04.832
You still wouldn't feel
quite right.

19:10.035 --> 19:12.433
I still don't think you
working here is a good idea.

19:12.467 --> 19:14.602
Why? Still
having dreams about me?

19:14.636 --> 19:16.404
No.

19:16.438 --> 19:18.706
How come I don't believe you?

19:28.036 --> 19:30.683
Are you freakin'
kidding me?

19:32.588 --> 19:36.475
- Hey, where are you going?
- You work here now, you can clean it up.

19:37.697 --> 19:40.249
- Hey, are you okay?
- I'm fine.

19:40.629 --> 19:43.715
She can be a <i>little</i> dramatic.

19:43.716 --> 19:45.631
Yeah, I noticed.

19:45.632 --> 19:48.041
Well, thank you for
making me do this tonight.

19:48.042 --> 19:49.859
I actually really
needed a night out.

19:49.860 --> 19:52.544
I'm glad I could help
take your mind off the...

19:52.608 --> 19:55.276
- Thing that we're not talking about.
- Mm-mm. (laughs)

19:55.311 --> 19:57.220
It's probably a little
overwhelming for you.

19:57.229 --> 20:00.137
No, I'm actually okay. I guess
I'm not that freaked out,

20:00.138 --> 20:02.434
because I know
my mom didn't do it.

20:04.186 --> 20:05.386
What?

20:06.758 --> 20:09.357
I know we said we wouldn't
talk about the case,

20:09.391 --> 20:12.960
but I give you permission...
dinner is technically over.

20:12.995 --> 20:17.248
Look, I'm just concerned that
you're not taking this very seriously.

20:17.299 --> 20:19.929
Maura Thatcher claims
that she saw your mother

20:19.930 --> 20:22.070
murder
her husband in cold blood.

20:22.675 --> 20:25.406
But people make mistakes.

20:25.441 --> 20:27.975
Especially in
traumatic situations.

20:28.010 --> 20:30.044
And I've read studies
where eyewitnesses

20:30.062 --> 20:34.108
claim to see a short woman that
was really a six-foot-two man.

20:34.109 --> 20:35.842
I know, I know, and
maybe you're right.

20:35.843 --> 20:37.727
I hope you're right.
I just think that...

20:37.808 --> 20:40.342
You need to prepare
yourself for the...

20:40.462 --> 20:43.272
The worst-case scenario.
That's all.

20:44.159 --> 20:46.827
Your mother could...
go to jail...

20:47.363 --> 20:49.564
For a long time.

20:49.598 --> 20:52.033
âª

20:53.502 --> 20:55.920
I should probably
be getting home.

20:55.954 --> 20:59.096
Ingrid... uh, Ingrid, no, let me pay,
and I can walk you.

20:59.097 --> 21:01.709
No. I'm fine.
I could use some fresh air.

21:01.710 --> 21:03.678
But thank you so much
for dinner.

21:03.712 --> 21:06.013
It was really nice.

21:16.975 --> 21:18.976
(heavy breathing)

21:31.568 --> 21:34.570
âª

21:57.744 --> 21:59.745
Hello, Joanna.

22:10.941 --> 22:13.626
(coughing and gasping)

22:38.819 --> 22:40.836
(panting)

22:41.838 --> 22:43.839
(murmurs)

22:49.812 --> 22:51.322
(muffled screaming)

22:51.713 --> 22:54.138
Joanna, stop...
Do you hear me?

22:54.185 --> 22:56.804
I will kill you.
Do you hear me?

22:56.838 --> 23:00.299
This is not over.
(muffled shouting)

23:00.338 --> 23:02.068
I will find you,
I'll kill you!

23:02.069 --> 23:03.703
I will haunt you...

23:13.288 --> 23:15.790
(sighs)

23:21.914 --> 23:24.720
The stories I could tell
about your mother.

23:24.721 --> 23:27.535
You would not believe
the stories that I could tell.

23:27.553 --> 23:30.157
But do I? No, uh-uh.

23:31.498 --> 23:35.518
Because I'm a good sister...
and I'm a good aunt,

23:35.519 --> 23:38.470
maybe not in this lifetime
but in other ones.

23:38.471 --> 23:40.793
I'm sure you were, and
I actually need to talk

23:40.794 --> 23:42.429
to my good aunt
about something.

23:42.430 --> 23:45.543
Ingrid, you're a natural.

23:46.238 --> 23:49.741
You always have been.
I don't want you to forget that.

23:49.775 --> 23:52.381
Um, that's actually what
I want to talk to you about.

23:52.382 --> 23:54.412
I've been thinking
about what you said...

23:54.446 --> 23:56.831
- Okay...
- And about how I can write spells.

23:56.865 --> 23:59.716
- No, n-n-no, it is not possible.
- Why not?

23:59.717 --> 24:03.087
Because there are some spells
that just can't be written.

24:03.122 --> 24:05.715
But you said I was a
spell-writing genius.

24:05.723 --> 24:08.259
Okay, Ingrid
from a hundred years ago,

24:08.293 --> 24:10.762
who had been practicing
magic her entire life,

24:10.796 --> 24:13.247
yes, spell-writing genius.

24:13.265 --> 24:16.270
Ingrid today, who's been
practicing witchcraft

24:16.271 --> 24:18.186
for about five minutes,
not so much.

24:18.220 --> 24:20.221
Okay, but what you may
not know about me is

24:20.255 --> 24:23.441
that I've actually been studying
witchcraft my whole life...

24:23.475 --> 24:26.093
(laughs)
...Academically, historically.

24:26.111 --> 24:28.270
- I even wrote a dissertation.
- Oh...

24:28.296 --> 24:30.984
- And I have books, lots of books.
- You have books?

24:30.985 --> 24:35.381
And in one of them, I think I may have
found a spell that could be tweaked.

24:35.382 --> 24:38.156
No, no, no, please, oh, you don't know
what you're talking about.

24:38.157 --> 24:40.742
Please do not tweak
any spells.

24:40.743 --> 24:44.945
Okay, in fact, do not cast any spells
without my supervision.

24:44.963 --> 24:46.798
It's dangerous.

24:46.832 --> 24:48.492
Okay?

24:48.929 --> 24:51.564
- Okay.
- Do you promise?

24:52.865 --> 24:54.568
I promise.

24:54.790 --> 24:56.290
Okay.

24:56.308 --> 25:00.178
We'll have another lesson tomorrow,
but if we're done here,

25:00.179 --> 25:03.634
there's a really cute guy over by the
pool table that I want to go play with.

25:08.970 --> 25:11.369
Hi.

25:13.992 --> 25:16.360
(Freya and Dash moaning)

25:18.280 --> 25:21.115
So, tell me,
what was more fun...

25:21.149 --> 25:23.287
this or fixing
that guy's heart today?

25:23.288 --> 25:26.548
Yeah, well, it's technically
called an aortic resection, but...

25:26.549 --> 25:28.339
I'm gonna go with this.

25:28.373 --> 25:32.493
Hey, do you mind if I go home tonight?
I know we talked about me staying over.

25:32.511 --> 25:35.296
Wow, I feel so used.

25:35.297 --> 25:36.550
(laughs)

25:36.565 --> 25:40.835
I'm sorry, I just... I feel
like my family needs me.

25:40.853 --> 25:42.186
No, you know what?
You're right.

25:42.221 --> 25:44.222
You, uh, you should be
with your mom right now.

25:44.273 --> 25:47.141
- I understand.
- Ugh, stop being so sweet.

25:47.175 --> 25:49.861
I know I'm being an ass, not
sharing my problems with you.

25:49.895 --> 25:52.681
Hey, you are not
being an ass.

25:52.682 --> 25:54.255
I get it if you
need some space.

25:54.263 --> 25:56.625
No, I don't need any space;
that's not it.

25:56.626 --> 26:00.321
I just...
things are complicated.

26:00.355 --> 26:01.706
What's complicated?

26:01.740 --> 26:06.160
(sighs) My family,
my life, everything.

26:07.132 --> 26:08.412
Hmm.

26:08.463 --> 26:10.715
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

26:10.749 --> 26:12.867
No, it's okay.

26:12.885 --> 26:16.137
Let's, uh, let's talk
about something else.

26:16.171 --> 26:18.539
- So, how was work?
- Weird.

26:18.540 --> 26:20.925
Your brother got
a job at the bar today.

26:20.976 --> 26:22.176
What?

26:22.210 --> 26:24.178
What is the deal with you guys?

26:24.212 --> 26:26.380
(sighing):
Oh, God.

26:26.398 --> 26:29.150
It's a...
it's a long story.

26:29.184 --> 26:31.018
I like long stories.

26:31.933 --> 26:34.054
Right.
(sighs)

26:34.055 --> 26:35.255
Uh...

26:36.491 --> 26:40.613
Look, I... I was
engaged once before.

26:40.614 --> 26:42.619
Okay, I know I should have
told you a long time ago,

26:42.623 --> 26:46.009
but I just didn't feel
like getting into it.

26:47.482 --> 26:49.921
Freya, say something.

26:49.955 --> 26:54.041
You didn't tell me this before because
you "didn't feel like getting into it"?

26:54.075 --> 26:55.760
I don't even think
about her anymore.

26:55.794 --> 26:58.482
All right, our, our relationship
is not like you and me.

26:58.483 --> 26:59.947
So what was it like, then?

26:59.982 --> 27:02.804
It doesn't matter, okay, we
never should have been engaged.

27:03.366 --> 27:05.252
All you need to know

27:05.270 --> 27:07.915
is that Killian slept with her
three months before our wedding,

27:07.916 --> 27:10.362
and that was pretty much
the last time I saw my brother,

27:10.401 --> 27:13.110
so that's the
deal with us.

27:13.145 --> 27:17.264
- Why, why would he...?
- Because that's what he does.

27:17.282 --> 27:19.422
Killian's always been the
black sheep of our family.

27:19.423 --> 27:22.806
I mean, he got kicked out of every
prep school on the East Coast, he...

27:22.807 --> 27:24.764
God, he can't hold a job
for more than a few months,

27:24.765 --> 27:26.721
he's never had a real
relationship with a woman,

27:26.722 --> 27:28.505
and for some reason
he blames me.

27:28.927 --> 27:32.113
Maybe it's because
I <i>didn't</i> screw up my life

27:32.147 --> 27:35.049
or because I take responsibility for
things, so going after my girlfriends...

27:35.083 --> 27:37.218
it's always been
like this little game to him.

27:37.252 --> 27:40.221
See what kind of damage
he can cause.

27:40.255 --> 27:44.458
I don't know, I-I guess
it's his revenge or something.

27:44.476 --> 27:46.460
So, he's done this
more than once?

27:46.470 --> 27:50.343
Not successfully, but yeah,
he always tries. It's pathetic.

27:50.671 --> 27:53.734
I wouldn't be surprised if
he's gearing up to hit on you.

27:58.634 --> 28:00.274
Hey.

28:00.308 --> 28:04.779
Babe, I am, I am so sorry.

28:04.813 --> 28:06.798
Okay, you know I love you.

28:07.983 --> 28:10.751
I know, I just... I think
I need to be alone right now.

28:10.786 --> 28:12.787
I'll call you tomorrow.

28:17.459 --> 28:19.994
"The price shall not be paid,

28:20.012 --> 28:23.297
my soul is free from bondage."

28:23.332 --> 28:27.101
Shit, what's the Latin word
for "bondage"?

28:27.135 --> 28:28.853
(gasps)

28:28.887 --> 28:30.388
<i>Servitute.</i>

28:30.439 --> 28:32.306
That sounds right.

28:32.340 --> 28:35.026
Okay.

28:38.146 --> 28:40.481
Here goes nothing.

28:43.068 --> 28:45.069
Ugh.

28:51.243 --> 28:54.078
<i>Pretium non solvatur,</i>

28:54.129 --> 28:58.883
<i>libera animam meam a servitute.</i>

28:58.917 --> 29:01.368
<i>Quia illud velle ita.</i>

29:01.386 --> 29:04.705
<i>Quia illud velle...</i>

29:04.723 --> 29:07.091
(gasping)

29:14.382 --> 29:16.934
(screaming, cries)

29:17.936 --> 29:21.695
(screaming):
Help...!

29:23.719 --> 29:25.720
(gasps)

29:28.441 --> 29:30.442
(footfalls approaching)

29:32.695 --> 29:34.813
Ingrid.

29:34.864 --> 29:36.448
<i>Vade, daemonia.</i>

29:36.482 --> 29:40.902
<i>Animas vestras
ad infernum remittitur.</i>

29:40.936 --> 29:43.971
<i>Dimittam... dimittam.</i>

29:43.972 --> 29:45.420
Aunt Wendy.

29:45.421 --> 29:47.728
<i>Dimittam, dimittam.</i>

29:47.729 --> 29:49.268
What are you doing here?

29:49.286 --> 29:52.621
I knew you wouldn't listen to me.
You're a lot like your mother that way.

29:52.622 --> 29:53.907
You're gonna be okay.

29:53.941 --> 29:56.009
<i>Sana glacies.</i>

29:56.043 --> 29:58.411
(Ingrid whimpering)

29:58.445 --> 30:00.446
<i>Sana glacies.</i>

30:02.333 --> 30:05.117
<i>Sana glacies.</i>
Stay with me.

30:05.135 --> 30:06.419
Thank you.

30:06.453 --> 30:11.391
<i>Sana glacies.</i>
<i>Sana glacies.</i>

30:18.349 --> 30:20.846
- What are you doing back here?
- Forgot my jacket.

30:21.185 --> 30:22.821
Okay, that's bullshit.

30:22.822 --> 30:25.321
I mean, I did forget my jacket,
but that is not why I'm here.

30:25.356 --> 30:28.121
I just wanted to look you in your face
when I told you this:

30:28.144 --> 30:29.756
I'm on to you.

30:29.967 --> 30:33.664
Would it shock you to know I have
no idea what you're talking about?

30:33.665 --> 30:36.199
I know why you've been pretending
you have all these feelings for me

30:36.200 --> 30:38.726
and that we have this deep connection,
but you can cut the crap.

30:38.727 --> 30:41.120
You and Dash need to work
out your problems yourselves.

30:41.121 --> 30:43.756
Or don't... I don't really care.
Just leave me out of it.

30:44.015 --> 30:46.148
You may have slept with one
fiancÃ©e,

30:46.149 --> 30:48.107
but you are never going
to sleep with this one.

30:48.108 --> 30:49.929
Are you done now?

30:49.964 --> 30:51.831
I notice you're not
denying anything.

30:51.849 --> 30:54.467
Look, I did sleep
with Elyse.

30:54.501 --> 30:56.436
Oh, why would you
tell me her name?

30:56.470 --> 30:59.138
But that was a long time ago, and for
the record, things in their relationship

30:59.172 --> 31:00.773
were pretty screwed up
to begin with.

31:00.808 --> 31:02.308
Oh, whatever... I know
you have tried to sleep

31:02.342 --> 31:04.560
with every woman
Dash has ever dated.

31:04.756 --> 31:07.487
- Is that what he told you?
- Is it the truth?

31:07.488 --> 31:09.365
Would you believe me
if I said it wasn't?

31:09.400 --> 31:12.858
- Why should I believe anything you say?
- Exactly.

31:16.490 --> 31:19.125
I haven't been
pretending, Freya.

31:20.377 --> 31:22.912
I don't know
how much clearer I can be.

31:23.209 --> 31:25.577
Do you really expect me
to fall for that?

31:25.611 --> 31:28.046
No, I don't expect anything
except for you to admit

31:28.047 --> 31:30.715
that there is a connection
here and we both know it.

31:33.286 --> 31:37.389
No, the only connection we have is
that we work together in this bar

31:37.423 --> 31:39.675
and I'm marrying
your brother.

31:39.726 --> 31:40.926
That's all.

31:42.824 --> 31:44.620
Good night.

32:07.453 --> 32:09.788
Mmm.

32:25.782 --> 32:28.951
Okay.

32:32.145 --> 32:33.445
Huh.

32:33.479 --> 32:35.814
(gasps)

32:39.852 --> 32:41.953
Who the hell are you?!

32:44.227 --> 32:46.311
(groans)

32:48.527 --> 32:50.195
(gasps)

32:50.213 --> 32:51.529
Mom?

32:51.547 --> 32:53.977
- Freya... use your powers.
- Freya, use your powers.

32:53.993 --> 32:57.861
Freya Eilif Beauchamp, you have
permission to use your powers!

33:15.688 --> 33:19.453
(Freya gasps,
Joanna sighs)

33:19.454 --> 33:21.393
Oh, my God, Mom,
are you okay?

33:21.394 --> 33:23.739
Oh, God. Are you all right?

33:23.740 --> 33:26.196
Yeah. Oh, what the hell!

33:26.199 --> 33:28.066
I thought you
took care of her.

33:28.084 --> 33:31.046
I sort of lied.

33:33.122 --> 33:37.242
FREYA: Why? Why do you always lie?

33:37.276 --> 33:41.589
- Why does everyone always lie?
- Who else is lying?

33:41.644 --> 33:45.238
Me. I'm lying
to Dash every single day.

33:45.285 --> 33:48.578
I'm hiding this huge thing from
him for the rest of our lives.

33:48.579 --> 33:49.967
How do I do that?

33:49.968 --> 33:54.855
How do I marry someone when I have
this giant secret about who I am?

33:54.890 --> 33:59.843
Because you're so much more
than just a witch, Freya.

33:59.861 --> 34:01.979
You're still the same smart,

34:02.014 --> 34:06.126
talented, caring and beautiful
woman that you've always been.

34:06.127 --> 34:08.946
And that's who Dash fell in love
with, and that hasn't changed.

34:10.522 --> 34:12.356
Okay.

34:12.373 --> 34:14.692
I love you, Freya.

34:14.710 --> 34:18.027
I know how strong you are,
and I know you can do this.

34:19.654 --> 34:21.821
That knife throw...

34:22.301 --> 34:24.534
That was pretty impressive.

34:24.534 --> 34:27.467
I know. I can't believe
it actually worked.

34:27.469 --> 34:29.907
That was the first time I've done
something like that on purpose.

34:29.942 --> 34:31.425
Finally!

34:31.476 --> 34:32.810
I'm proud of you, baby.

34:32.844 --> 34:35.313
- Thanks.
- You did good.

34:35.347 --> 34:39.266
With a little practice, you'll gain
greater control of your gifts.

34:39.318 --> 34:41.686
Ooh, does that mean you're
actually gonna let me practice?

34:41.719 --> 34:44.688
Ooh, does that mean
I could have stopped you?

34:44.723 --> 34:47.768
It's time, and you're ready.

34:47.770 --> 34:52.512
I'm not, but I wasn't ready
for you to start dating...

34:52.513 --> 34:54.031
In any century.

34:54.032 --> 34:56.283
And I couldn't stop you
then, either

34:56.293 --> 34:59.264
- Come...
- I love you, Mom.

34:59.265 --> 35:01.817
Mm.
(sighs)

35:02.040 --> 35:04.908
Hey, didn't you burn that?

35:06.261 --> 35:08.379
I did.

35:08.413 --> 35:12.466
You're not the only one
in this house with cool powers.

35:12.517 --> 35:14.760
Oh.

35:22.713 --> 35:23.978
Sorry.

35:24.490 --> 35:26.697
You missed last call.

35:26.732 --> 35:30.708
For the record, I know exactly
what you're up to.

35:30.731 --> 35:32.603
Oh, well, maybe you
do, maybe you don't.

35:32.621 --> 35:35.539
Either way, it has no
effect on me or my plans.

35:35.574 --> 35:38.173
Yeah, well, look, I'm thinking maybe
you should change your plans.

35:38.174 --> 35:40.402
'Cause you won't win this
one, Killian, I promise.

35:40.481 --> 35:42.182
I don't want you
getting hurt.

35:42.183 --> 35:44.864
Appreciate the concern.
I'll take it under advisement.

35:44.883 --> 35:48.339
Fine. You know, you
just do your thing.

35:48.340 --> 35:51.305
Play it as cool as you want,
pretend nothing bothers you.

35:51.306 --> 35:55.459
But the real Killian
always shows himself eventually.

35:55.477 --> 35:57.762
And that's
when it all goes wrong.

35:57.796 --> 36:01.232
Oh, yeah?
What about the real you?

36:01.266 --> 36:03.517
You told Freya
what I did five years ago,

36:03.568 --> 36:05.478
but did you tell her
the rest of the story?

36:07.272 --> 36:08.989
(motorcycle engine revving)

36:09.024 --> 36:10.741
Yeah.

36:10.776 --> 36:12.993
Didn't think so.

36:13.028 --> 36:16.447
(engine revving)

36:16.481 --> 36:19.983
They still feel
really cold.

36:20.001 --> 36:21.952
(sighs)

36:21.986 --> 36:24.655
It's gonna take a few more minutes
before they're normal again.

36:24.673 --> 36:27.842
Don't worry.
You're gonna be okay.

36:27.876 --> 36:31.791
That was just
so awful, scary.

36:31.807 --> 36:34.882
Did you really feel that you could
just pull something like this off

36:34.933 --> 36:36.834
after knowing
you're a witch for a week?

36:36.852 --> 36:41.105
I guess I wasn't thinking.
I just wanted to do something.

36:41.106 --> 36:42.802
I don't want someone to die.

36:42.809 --> 36:46.695
I know, but putting yourself
in danger is not the answer.

36:47.643 --> 36:51.189
I really can't change
this curse, can I?

36:51.190 --> 36:54.526
What's destined to happen will happen.
It's already in motion.

36:54.736 --> 36:56.537
And you can't spend
every day

36:56.571 --> 36:59.206
worrying about it, or you're
gonna drive yourself crazy.

36:59.241 --> 37:01.024
I know.

37:02.358 --> 37:04.984
You have to live your life.
(door opening)

37:05.023 --> 37:06.831
ADAM:
Hello?

37:06.865 --> 37:08.632
Hello.
(door closes)

37:08.667 --> 37:12.703
Oh, I, uh... I saw your car,
so I figured you might still be here.

37:15.092 --> 37:17.427
I will see you at home.

37:19.260 --> 37:21.192
Adam.

37:22.898 --> 37:25.412
Before you say anything,
I just...

37:27.269 --> 37:30.579
- I just want to apologize.
- You don't have to do that.

37:30.580 --> 37:34.276
It's not like we can pretend
this stuff with my mom isn't happening.

37:34.277 --> 37:36.162
I could have been
more sensitive.

37:36.163 --> 37:38.364
You shouldn't have
to walk on eggshells.

37:39.781 --> 37:42.249
I just think...

37:42.284 --> 37:44.919
Maybe we missed our window.

37:44.953 --> 37:48.906
You know, maybe we should have
done this a long time ago

37:48.924 --> 37:50.875
when things were simpler.

37:50.909 --> 37:53.210
Maybe it's too late now.

37:53.244 --> 37:57.056
Or... maybe you know your mom
better than me,

37:57.057 --> 37:58.903
and I should have just
shut up about it.

37:58.904 --> 38:04.230
Adam, it's just, my life
is so complicated right now,

38:04.231 --> 38:07.274
and I don't think you should
subject yourself to that.

38:07.309 --> 38:09.927
I'm a big boy.

38:09.945 --> 38:11.929
And I know
my timing's not the best,

38:11.947 --> 38:14.648
but I have waited too long
to have our first date,

38:14.699 --> 38:18.319
and I don't want
to wait any more for our second.

38:18.370 --> 38:21.602
If that even counts
as a first date. It...

38:28.613 --> 38:30.915
I think it does now.

38:39.424 --> 38:42.793
WENDY: So Freya really sent
the knife across the kitchen?

38:42.811 --> 38:44.345
- Mm-hmm, mm.
- That's great!

38:44.396 --> 38:47.307
I mean, it's not great that the shifter
broke through your protection spell.

38:47.308 --> 38:50.234
I was just so out of
practice, I was overwhelmed.

38:50.235 --> 38:53.303
And you couldn't tell anything about
the shifter? About who it was?

38:53.321 --> 38:54.822
No, not a thing.

38:54.856 --> 38:58.692
Only that they were good
and fast and looked like me,

38:58.743 --> 39:00.744
only, I think
I have better hair.

39:00.779 --> 39:02.312
You do have
really great hair.

39:02.330 --> 39:03.831
Thanks.

39:04.361 --> 39:09.653
Okay, this is really hard for me
to say, but I think you were right.

39:09.671 --> 39:12.256
Don't say anything! Don't.

39:12.290 --> 39:15.376
I <i>do</i> have trouble
letting people help me.

39:15.427 --> 39:18.661
It's like I'm a little bit
set in my ways.

39:18.662 --> 39:21.405
Okay, I'm a lot
set in my ways.

39:21.429 --> 39:25.335
So maybe I need to loosen up,
enjoy it all more.

39:25.353 --> 39:27.004
I can certainly
help you with that.

39:27.022 --> 39:28.505
(laughter)

39:28.523 --> 39:31.569
And maybe I need to grow
up just-just a little bit.

39:31.595 --> 39:33.110
- Mm-hmm.
- But not too much,

39:33.111 --> 39:35.529
